The Telegraph - Calcutta : Frontpage
 Thursday, February 05, 2004 				 Panel punch to colas
																								New Delhi, Feb. 4: The joint parliamentary committee set up to probe pesticide levels in soft drinks has upheld the findings of the Centre for Science and Environment and asked the government to lay down stringent norms for carbonated drinks.																								The panels report said the CSE stands corroborated on its findings on pesticide residues in 12 brand products of Pepsi and Coca-Cola, prompting the two companies to assert that their beverages produced in India were safe.																								The JPC report said the committee had sent samples to two labs. Both the laboratories detected the presence of organochlorine and organophosphorous pesticide residues. 
